gomodel:SYNGO_5583  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CD47-SIRPα interaction prevents excess pruning during development, where CD47 serves as a \"don't eat me\" signal on synapses.\n\nFigure 2: Microglia in the CD47KO dLGN exhibit increased engulfment.\n\nFigure 3: CD47 knockout mice have reduced numbers of Vglut2-positive retinogeniculate synapses.\n\nFigure 6: Neuronal CD47 and microglial SIRPα are both required to specifically reduce engulfment of CD47-expressing synaptosomes.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Immunohistochemistry\nImmunohistochemistry was performed as described in Schafer et al., 2012. Briefly, brains and eyes were harvested from mice following\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
